t the likely cause is observational biases, such as limited\nsensitivity due to the high background from unresolved stars in the GC and\nlimited angular resolution of the telescopes used. We additionally detected one\nstrongly variable source in 47 Tuc, which could be identified as the known RR\nLyrae star HV 810. We found its period to have significantly increased with\nrespect to that measured from data taken in 1988.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Jan 2020 14:47:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-26"}
